SIMPLE: systemic
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Systemic
<hw>Sys*tem"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or
relating to a system; common to a system; <as>as, the <ex>systemic</ex>
circulation of the blood</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Anat. & Physiol.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to
the general system, or the body as a whole; <as>as, <ex>systemic</ex>
death, in distinction from <xex>local</xex> death; <ex>systemic</ex>
circulation, in distinction from <xex>pulmonic</xex> circulation;
<ex>systemic</ex> diseases</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Systemic death</b></col>. <cd>See the Note under
<er>Death</er>, <pos>n.</pos>, 1.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Systemization</ent>⟦br⟧
